The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Rivlin of Israel and Vice President Pence of the United States during a meeting in Jerusalem. President Rivlin thanks Vice President Pence for his support of Israel and for recognizing Jerusalem as its capital. He discusses the historical and cultural significance of Jerusalem and expresses hope for peace negotiations. Vice President Pence reaffirms the United States' commitment to Israel and discusses security collaboration, the threat of Iran, and the desire for peace. The two leaders also plan to discuss Syria and Gaza.